lines.text: I mean, what if Dyanna...
Don't you get tired of always being the responsible one? Why don't you let somebody else do the thinking?
You always know just what to say to me...
The feeling's mutual.
You had that crowd under your thumb.
It was an easy crowd!
You know, what happened between Janine and Asia was kinda like an accident.
Yeah right! Oh, and I suppose Asia just tripped and fell right into Janine's pussy.
the straps on her dress]
Will you come over here and help me with this?
Thought you'd never ask...
[Dyanna is talking to Asia, a piano player]
You ever have one of those nights - where you don't do anything wrong - but you still feel like you could've done better?
Only when I play piano.
I had a feeling I'd find you two here... in Janine's little hide-out.
[to Asia]
Old habits are hard to break, aren't they? Here.
[she tosses a package onto the bed]
What's that?
It's a recording contract... but you're going to be needing to find a new singer!
